Posted: Wed Nov 07, 2012 7:00 pm
Polo shirt, dark jeans, and you'll be fine. The running shoes are a bit iffy though. You could hit up a store and rent some shoes though (Moores?), heck you could rent the whole outfit if you wanted.I pretty firmly dress for comfort first, style second. My shirts are in good repair, not faded, and clean. The closest I get to a "business casual" shirt is a short sleeve button up shirt with a straight cut bottom untucked, or perhaps a casual long sleeve shirt (and no, not the wool sweater over a dress shirt look, I just can't handle that).Again, its all about comfort. I'm not comfortable in long sleeves indoors because I like it to be about 19-21C tops, not 23-25 C like most places in the winter. And jackets / blazers? Forget it.Besides. Even if I were to dress up, my epic beard and middle of back length hair don't really go Wear clothes, be polite, you'll be fine.EDIT: And I have to say, thanks to my Dad for pushing me to get some "walking shoes", specifically Rockports, as my every day shoe. They're comfortable, not dress shoes, flat black, and work with everything except dress pants, but since I don't wear those - I'm good - CG
