Posted: Wed Nov 07, 2012 7:29 pm
To Echo: Khakis or Non-Jean Pants (with pockets at the hip only), Non-Athletic/Non-Sandal Shoes - if plain leather, polished. (Good excuse to buy yourself a pair of boots for winter) If Suede... not tatty. A Shirt with a collar (Roll neck sweater works, but be prepared to be accused of missing a beret and mustache)You never know who you might meet, and business casual is pretty comfortable and looks much better than jeans and any athletic shoes IMNSHO.Or A nice pair of Jeans and a collared shirt + jacket + boots looks pretty decent too - but it's not business casual.Also, the lounge is not your for-pay-boardroom.So here's a lesson on problem solving:
